-- Kan's Approval Rating Falls Two Points to 48% in Japan, Asahi Survey Says
-- Kazuyo Sawa
-- 2010-06-27T22:27:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-27/kan-s-approval-rating-falls-two-points-to-48-in-japan-asahi-survey-says.html

          
          
             Japanese Prime Minister Naoto Kan
has an approval rating of 48 percent in an Asahi newspaper
survey taken June 26-27, down 2 percentage points from June
19-20. His disapproval rating rose 2 points to 29 percent.  
 Support for Kan’s Democratic Party of Japan was 37 percent,
up 5 percentage points. The support level for the opposition
Liberal Democratic Party rose 1 point to 14 percent, the
newspaper said.  
 The Asahi took the survey by telephone and obtained 1,023
valid responses. The newspaper didn’t provide a margin of error.  
